      "content": "The ideal customer is likely a self-made, established figure, probably a successful business owner or executive, often with a background in finance or industry. They value exclusivity, heritage, and the visible display of their success, seeing the watch not just as timekeeping but as a status symbol. They appreciate craftsmanship, but only when it aligns with a certain established, often traditional, sense of elite taste. They are discerning, but their discernment is rooted in inherited or acquired markers of old-world power.",
